[183.976222, "o", "✅ **Task completed successfully!**\r\n\r\n**Files created:**\r\n- `/app/airline_analysis.py` - Python script that solves the problem\r\n- `/app/results.txt` - Contains the answer: `80`\r\n\r\n**Answer:** The greatest positive integer d is **80**.\r\n\r\nThis means that no matter how the three airlines schedule their departures (with periods of 100, 120, and 150 days), there will always be at least **80 consecutive days** without any flight from Dodola island.\r\n"]
